 :tx/rationale "UAQ-9 REVISION: The A/B test is now richer. Three composition variants to test: (A) Cost-aware alpha = E[delta_F(S)] / cost — the ADR-019 formulation. (B) Cost-blind product = impact * relevance * novelty * confidence — the original UAQ v1 formulation. (C) Cost-aware weighted-sum = (w1*impact + w2*relevance + w3*novelty + w4*confidence) / cost. The A/B test during external dog-food should measure which produces lowest mean prediction error and highest productive action rate. The formulation defaults to (A) — this is the theoretically correct one. But empirical validation may show that (B) is simpler and good enough, or that (C) allows factor compensation that (A) vetoes. The config datom :policy/acquisition-composition with values 'alpha', 'product', 'weighted-sum' selects the variant. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-025, INV-FOUNDATION-011."
